What kind of Information we collect?
Booking the perfect trip requires essential information from you, so we may require certain types of information, which fall into the following categories:
Personal Information:
This includes details such as your name, email address, phone number, and other contact information. Additionally, we may ask about your travel preferences, like preferred destinations and travel dates, to tailor our services better to your needs.
Aggregate Data:
This category comprises information that doesn't personally identify you. It encompasses data about the number of visitors to our website, the pages they visit, and the search terms they use. This helps us understand overall usage patterns and improve our services.
Information about Your Location:
We may collect data concerning your physical location, particularly when you utilize our services to search for flights or hotels. This information assists us in providing location-specific results and recommendations.
It's essential to note that we may also augment the information we collect from you with data obtained from other companies, all while adhering to our Privacy Statement and applicable data protection laws. Safeguarding your privacy remains our priority, and we will handle all information with the utmost care and transparency.
How we use your Information?
We use the information we collect for various purposes to enhance your experience and provide you with the best possible service. These purposes include, but are not limited to:
Booking Services:
The personal information you provide allows us to process bookings for flights, hotels, and other travel services you request. This enables us to facilitate smooth and efficient travel arrangements on your behalf.
Personalization:
Understanding your travel preferences helps us tailor our recommendations and offerings to match your specific interests and needs. By analyzing your past travel behavior, we can suggest relevant destinations, accommodations, and activities that align with your preferences.
Customer Support:
Your contact information enables us to respond to inquiries, provide support, and assist you with any issues or concerns you may encounter during your trip planning or booking process.
Improvement of Services:
By analyzing aggregate data and user behavior, we can gain insights into the effectiveness and usability of our application and services. This information allows us to continuously improve and optimize our offerings to better serve our customers.
Marketing and Communication:
We may use your email address or phone number to send you promotional offers, updates, and newsletters, but only if you have provided explicit consent or as permitted by applicable laws.
Security and Fraud Prevention:
Personal data helps us identify and prevent fraudulent activities, ensuring a secure environment for all users of our platform.
Legal Compliance:
In some cases, we may need to use your information to comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, or enforce our terms and conditions.
It is essential to reiterate that we value your privacy, and your information will only be used in accordance with our Privacy Policy and applicable data protection laws. We will not disclose your personal data to third parties without your consent, except as necessary for the provision of our services or as required by law.
Why we share your Information?
We have various parties involved in our services, each integrated in different ways and for different purposes. The main objective behind sharing your data is to furnish the Booking provider with the necessary information to finalize your reservation.
We only share Personal Information with third parties under specific and limited circumstances:
With Your Consent:
Your booking details may be shared with the booking provider to complete your reservation and process your payment, but only with your explicit consent.
Third-Party Service Providers:
We may share your information with vendors, consultants, and service providers who collaborate with us and require access to your data to carry out their responsibilities.
Legal Compliance:
Information may be disclosed to adhere to applicable laws or respond to lawful requests and legal processes.
Protection of Rights:
We may share information to safeguard the rights and property of
Last Minute Hotel Booking
, our agents, customers, and others, including the enforcement of our agreements, policies, and terms of use.
Emergency Situations:
In emergency scenarios, information may be disclosed to ensure the personal safety of
Last Minute Hotel Booking
, its customers, or individuals.
Business Transactions:
Personal information may be shared concerning business-related transactions, such as mergers, acquisitions, bankruptcies, or asset transfers.
Children's Privacy
Last Minute Hotel Booking
is a service for adults over the age of 16. We do not process information about children under the age of 16 without the consent of their parents or legal guardians. If you are under the age of 16, you can only use this service if your parents or legal guardians have given their consent.
If you are a parent or guardian and become aware that your child has shared personal information with us without your consent, please contact us immediately at
